Tomcat4.0b1 (Catalina) JDBCRealm.Digest(..) method applies a Base64 encoding on top of a hex encoding, where Tomcat3.3m2 applies a simple hex encoding. They should be the same (I think 3.3m2 has it right).

4.0b1
>Base64 enc=new Base64();
>return new String(enc.encode(HexUtils.convert(dig).getBytes()));

3.3m2
>return HexUtils.convert(dig);
